                  </hi>, <hi rend="italic">of Down-street, Piccadilly.</hi> On the 23rd of Jan., about two o'clock, the prisoner came for half-a-pound of soap—he gave me a half-crown—I gave him change—as soon as he left, I found the half-crown was bad—I locked it in my desk by itself—he came again on the 30th of Jan. for half-a-pound of soap, and gave me a 5<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. piece—I found it was bad, and gave him into custody, with the half-crown and crown-piece.</p>
